          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-30 14:54:03" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:δαπανάω&lt;SDBG:δαπανάω:000000&gt;}[a] ‘‘to spend,’ {D:57.146}) to exert great effort in doing something</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to do anything</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to exert great effort</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is possible, however, that δαπανάω in {S:04701201500008} should be understood in the literal sense and hence rendered ‘I will be glad to spend all I have on your behalf’ (see {L:δαπανάω&lt;SDBG:δαπανάω:000000&gt;}[a] {D:57.146}).</Comments>
